The code can be run using the following 3 parameters:
$ python ass1.py 1.1
$ python ass1.py 1.2
$ python ass1.py 1.3
Which will give you the results of the corresponding sub assignments.

It is assumed that the test/training data is located in the same folder as the program.

To run the code, NumPy needs to be installed, this can be installed with
pythons package manager with the following command:
$ pip install numpy
